40|$|Examines {{the role}} played by the concept of {{possession}} in the common law tradition and the extent of its significance in the twenty-first century. Considers the early law concept <b>of</b> <b>seisin,</b> the principles <b>of</b> possession in modern law and the operation of original acquisition rules in modern property law. Discusses the concept of adverse possession of land, including the House of Lords ruling in JA Pye (Oxford) Ltd v Graham, the relationship between adverse possession and human rights law and the impact of the Land Registration Act 2002...|$|R
